HEADWORD: Nutgall
<hw>Nut"gall`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A more or less round
gall resembling a nut, esp. one of those produced on the oak and used in
the arts. See <er>Gall</er>, <er>Gallnut</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

